<br>
  First off you don't want to go to the desert solo.  The mobs will eat you alive (and your pet).  You can duo with another mage in the desert chaining pets, or with a shammy, but don't attempt them solo.  Would not be worth the effort.<br>
<br>
  As far as getting adds, yeah they suck.  There really isn't a trick to it, all I can say is you get better as you do it and learn a lot about the zone from continued attempts.<br>
<br>
  For instance the first few times I did trees I had adds every other one, sucked, and I got frustrated.  After awhile you basically learn which tree spawn points have ZERO adds, which tree spawn points have a SLIGHT chance for adds, and which tree spawn point you shuld not even bother with because you will ALWAYS get an add.  Off the top of my I can think of about 5 tree spots where you 95% of the time get an add.  My solution ? Don't do those trees, just leave em.  If I&quot;m doing with a mage I'll kill em cause we kill twice as fast and an add isn't a problem, but solo I simply skip em.  You learn from trial and error like I said.<br>
<br>
   There are always I think 5 tree spawn spots where I know I am completely safe and can kill with no adds.  Whenever I see them up its free exp.  The rest and majority of them, you just need to learn the pathing, once again trial and error.  You just need to have an idea of what directions the adds come from at that tree.  Then just go into 3rd person view and get a GOOD look all around and make sure none inc.  Then send pet, malosini, and chain nuke FBOT fast before one does come.<br>
<br>
   I could let pet solo them to 40% then just burn it down at end, but that would take too long and would most likely get an add.  So I just chain nuke from the start to kill them as fast as possible.  GL Shonine if you try again.  <br>
<br>
Lianad Staffborn<br>
62 mage Bertoxx<br>
<br>
P.S. As far as bears and flowers etc, I would not recommend killing any of them out in the middle of the zone.  The only time I kill bears, or flowers is when one paths near a wall and I just kill it there.  It is almost impossible to pull them as well, so you pretty much have to just kill them in place, which if is in the middle of the zone is very dangerous... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=calfhigh>Calfhigh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(1/22/03 8:01:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> A side note as to the elders and chieftens of the bees/vulture type things i can clear that up.<br>
If you clear all of the bees in the zone you spawn 4 elders/cheiftens in a mix, they are un splittable, and corpse camp.  You manage to kill them ( 2 group minimum ) 4 more spawn, you kill those 4 and get the boss bee, hits for 1481 and rampages.<br>
